			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We'd like to support the &amp;quot;gclient --git-deps&amp;quot; mode, aka &amp;quot;new git workflow&amp;quot; described at http://code.google.com/p/chromium/wiki/UsingNewGit  (for the chromium repo).

This requires some infrastructure support and some cleanup of native_client/DEPS.

1. Consolidate DEPS to have fewer separate entries, since each one translates into a git mirror repository.

2. Don't use File() in DEPS.  This is blocked on http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=102682

3. Get the infrastructure team's scripts to handle the native_client repo URLs needed, and to do repo synch'ing and .DEPS.git generation in their cron jobs.
